I can't be checking the sites with TWO jobs at the same time, so I need a DB entry that will keep track of if it's checking the sites right now. (is_checking_sites)

```
@periodic(minute='0-59/2')
def check_sites(self):
    check = self.load(""is_checking_sites"", False)
    if check is False:
        return False
    self.save(""is_checking_sites"", True)
    for site in sites:
        self._check_site(site)
```
Now if Will is restarted in the middle of the job, ""is_checking_sites"" is stuck as False and will have to manually be cleared.

I want him to be able to reset ""is_checking_sites"" to False when Will is started.

I was thinking about somehow having Redis expire the key after X seconds, but that seems kind of flaky and imperfect. I'd like to save that as a sort of last resort.


Thanks for the reply @skoczen !",{},,User,False
