1075,IssueCommentEvent,2016-12-07 15:06:48+00:00,28530868,cannatag/ldap3,1319333,cannatag,,,193897000,265470957,"Thanks, will update the docs. Starting from version 2 ldap3 reads the schema by default so it is aware of the single or multi valued property of each attribute and this is reflected in the attributes dictionary.

> Il giorno 06 dic 2016, alle ore 22:57, James Laird-Wah <notifications@github.com> ha scritto:
> 
> The documentation describes the connection.response dicts' attributes:
> attributes: a dictionary of returned attributes and their values. Values are list. Values are in UTF-8 format
> 
> Since commit 8e30080 that is no longer the case, at least in Python2. Single-valued attributes are unicode strings rather than lists:
> 
> {'attributes': {u'distinguishedName': u'CN=James Laird-Wah,OU=XXX,DC=XXX'},
>  'dn': u'CN=James Laird-Wah,OU=XXX,DC=XXX',
>  'raw_attributes': {u'distinguishedName': ['CN=James Laird-Wah,OU=XXX,DC=XXX']},
>  'type': 'searchResEntry'}
> The raw_attributes entry is unaffected.
> 
> —
> You are receiving this because you are subscribed to this thread.
> Reply to this email directly, view it on GitHub, or mute the thread.
> 
",{},,User,False
