1377,IssueCommentEvent,2017-03-21 14:19:23+00:00,21006723,pmorissette/bt,409035,pmorissette,,,213445208,288092522,"Hi Tim,

I haven't tried doing anything similar myself, but I think your approach should work. Basically, you could create a custom algo that would take a DataFrame of dividends (same size as the price DataFrame), and decide what to do with the dividends on a daily basis. 

If you want it to impact the performance, then you can do something similar to the `bt.algos.CapitalFlow`, but change the call from `target.adjust(amount)` to `target.adjust(amount, flow=False)`. I just updated the docstring in `bt.core.StrategyBase.adjust` for the `flow` param. Basically, if it is set to False, the adjustment will have an impact on performance. 

Hope this helps, and please report back if you implement this successfully. I'm sure others will be interested. 

Cheers,
Phil",{},,User,False
