1424,IssueCommentEvent,2016-11-03 03:35:43+00:00,19361153,tdryer/hangups,857374,tdryer,,,186619908,258058347,"`Client` currently doesn't support `connect` being called more than once, so after a disconnect you will need to re-instantiate it.

I think to fix the event loop errors you have to do something like this:
```python
task = asyncio.async(client.connect())
try:
    loop.run_until_complete(task)
except:
    task.cancel()
    loop.run_forever()
finally:
    loop.close()
```",{},,User,False
