2035,IssueCommentEvent,2018-08-08 00:47:52+00:00,94554082,dylanaraps/pywal,11150153,deviantfero,,,348525478,411248030,"this expected behaviour @amineden, `pywal` tries to be as non-intrusive as possible, and it accomplishes this by having it's own .Xres format output somewhere else, xrdb doesn't really care where the color-scheme actually is when you call it explicitly, you can find this outputs i'm talking about under `~/.cache/wal/colors.Xresources`

