2036,IssueCommentEvent,2017-08-12 02:17:12+00:00,94554082,dylanaraps/pywal,6799467,dylanaraps,,,249048502,321951315,"The `dict` is unsorted but we loop over it in a way which keeps the order.

Instead of:

```py
for index, color in enumerate(colors[""colors""]):
    set_color(index, color)
```

We now loop with:

```py
for index in range(16):
    set_color(index, colors[""colors""][""color%s"" % index])
```

The new way is more explicit and doesn't care if the dict is out of order. I'm not sure why it's not working on your system, are you using the latest version of this branch? 

Anyway, I'll write some tests to make sure the order is the same. This way we'll know if we break it. :)",{},,User,False
