2421,IssueCommentEvent,2018-04-22 17:47:39+00:00,90668463,davidhalter/parso,55281,ambv,,,316441714,383399283,"> ""official"" tokenize.py
You mean tokenizer.c?

The builtin CPython tokenizer accepts ""whatever"" as a name but later it runs the identifier through `verify_identifier()` which performs the PyUnicode_IsIdentifier check (you can find that in Objects/unicodeobject.c). That check does the full PEP 3131 verification of the first character and the rest.

For lib2to3 I won't implement the entire PEP 3131 check because frankly it's annoyingly complex. The regex I suggested above is ""good enough"" in that it's missing a relatively small number of code points (notably the legacy Other_ID_Start and Other_ID_Continue groups). To be closer to PEP 3131, I further verify [the initial character is in allowed classes](https://github.com/ambv/black/blob/master/blib2to3/pgen2/tokenize.py#L509-L510).",{},NONE,User,False
2423,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-29 12:45:32+00:00,90668463,davidhalter/parso,8318231,robodair,,,269078627,340259850,Good enough for me!,{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
2424,IssueCommentEvent,2018-05-27 01:05:06+00:00,90668463,davidhalter/parso,31109952,apnewberry,,,326383671,392297952,"FWIW, the two `tokenize` functions handle these strings pretty differently:

```python
def print_tokens(s):
    version = (3,6)
    pprint('parso:')
    pprint(list(parso.python.tokenize.tokenize(s, version)))
    pprint('stdlib:')
    pprint(string_to_tokens(s))

s1 = 'a + ? + b'
s2 = 'f""{a + ? + b}""'
print_tokens(s1)

'parso:'
[TokenInfo(type=NAME, string='a', start_pos=(1, 0), prefix=''),
 TokenInfo(type=PLUS, string='+', start_pos=(1, 2), prefix=' '),
 TokenInfo(type=ERRORTOKEN, string='? + b', start_pos=(1, 4), prefix=' '),
 TokenInfo(type=ENDMARKER, string='', start_pos=(1, 9), prefix='')]
'stdlib:'
[TokenInfo(type=59 (BACKQUOTE), string='utf-8', start=(0, 0), end=(0, 0), line=''),
 TokenInfo(type=1 (NAME), string='a', start=(1, 0), end=(1, 1), line='a + ? + b'),
 TokenInfo(type=53 (OP), string='+', start=(1, 2), end=(1, 3), line='a + ? + b'),
 TokenInfo(type=56 (ERRORTOKEN), string=' ', start=(1, 3), end=(1, 4), line='a + ? + b'),
 TokenInfo(type=56 (ERRORTOKEN), string='?', start=(1, 4), end=(1, 5), line='a + ? + b'),
 TokenInfo(type=53 (OP), string='+', start=(1, 6), end=(1, 7), line='a + ? + b'),
 TokenInfo(type=1 (NAME), string='b', start=(1, 8), end=(1, 9), line='a + ? + b'),
 TokenInfo(type=0 (ENDMARKER), string='', start=(2, 0), end=(2, 0), line='')]

print_tokens(s2)

'parso:'
[TokenInfo(type=FSTRING_START, string='f""', start_pos=(1, 0), prefix=''),
 TokenInfo(type=LBRACE, string='{', start_pos=(1, 2), prefix=''),
 TokenInfo(type=NAME, string='a', start_pos=(1, 3), prefix=''),
 TokenInfo(type=PLUS, string='+', start_pos=(1, 5), prefix=' '),
 TokenInfo(type=ERRORTOKEN, string='? + b}""', start_pos=(1, 7), prefix=' '),
 TokenInfo(type=ENDMARKER, string='', start_pos=(1, 14), prefix='')]
'stdlib:'
[TokenInfo(type=59 (BACKQUOTE), string='utf-8', start=(0, 0), end=(0, 0), line=''),
 TokenInfo(type=3 (STRING), string='f""{a + ? + b}""', start=(1, 0), end=(1, 14), line='f""{a + ? + b}""'),
 TokenInfo(type=0 (ENDMARKER), string='', start=(2, 0), end=(2, 0), line='')]

```",{},NONE,User,False
