2457,IssueCommentEvent,2018-02-13 18:51:30+00:00,5934517,dpkp/kafka-python,2299896,griff122,,,141744291,365365930,"Another cause for this issue is using a `bytes` object as the topic name, instead of a string. In python 3, you could have a string come in as a bytes object (`a = b'test_string'`). If this happens, you can just convert the topic name to a utf-8 string, and it might start working. It worked for me. 

```
if type(kafka_topic) == bytes:
    kafka_topic = kafka_topic.decode('utf-8')
kafka_producer = KafkaProducer(bootstrap_servers=kafka_brokers)
kafka_producer.send(kafka_topic, payload)
kafka_producer.flush()
```",{},NONE,User,False
