2866,IssueCommentEvent,2015-09-03 11:53:48+00:00,1938370,Mottie/tablesorter,136959,Mottie,,,104652848,137415961,"Hi @don750421!

Don't use ""updateAll"" unless the header changes.

I'm sorry I can't read the language in the screenshot. If the user is changing the value of the table directly inside the table, then all you would need is to trigger an update. If the user is changing the value in that dropdown, then you'll need to add the changes into the table, then trigger an ""update"":

```js
// target the cell and add the new data
$('td.toUpdate1').html( newData1 );
// ...
$('td.toUpdateN').html( newDataN );

// trigger update after all cells have been updated
$('table').trigger('update');
```
",{},,User,False
