3175,IssueCommentEvent,2018-06-15 23:07:53+00:00,6794278,scanny/python-pptx,2062718,scanny,,,323589013,397763655,"This is due to a behavior of PowerPoint, that it doesn't refresh chart data on chart open. Rather it uses the values cached in the chart.xml file (e.g. chart2.xml) to render the chart.

If you want the behavior you're asking for, you'll need to hack a bit further and update those values as well.

You'd be on your own for that work, but as far as pointers, I'd take a close look at the `Chart.replace_data()` method and see if I could make that work or adapt it.

Maybe you could replace the data with your new values using a suitably loaded `ChartData` object, and the update the Xlsx blob after that.",{},OWNER,User,False
