3394,IssueCommentEvent,2017-08-01 03:11:54+00:00,1897743,asweigart/pyperclip,13773950,catinsunshine,,,246941316,319255739,"Pls ignore it. Just find the solution.

The default Python 3 version in Debian is 3.5. Seems pip3 will install into 3.5. So, when I installed 3.6, need install pyperclip with below command:

```
peter@Debian:~$ python3.6 -m pip install pyperclip
Successfully installed pyperclip-1.5.27
```
Docs refer:
[https://docs.python.org/3/installing/index.html?highlight=pip#work-with-multiple-versions-of-python-installed-in-parallel](https://docs.python.org/3/installing/index.html?highlight=pip#work-with-multiple-versions-of-python-installed-in-parallel)",{},,User,False
