3405,IssueCommentEvent,2017-03-08 08:13:15+00:00,12406971,bastibe/PySoundFile,649181,bastibe,,,212636168,284975385,"Sorry to hear your tale. We changed the name from pysoundfile to soundfile a while ago, and keep pysoundfile around for compatibility reasons only. In fact, `pip install soundfile` is the preferred method for installing PySoundFile. 

The Python packaging ecosystem has only very recently embraced wheels far enough to make `pip install soundfile` work reliably.

Apparently, `pip install pysoundfile` was still mentioned at one place in the README. I have changed this. Also, I updated the README to hopefully be clearer and prevent more people from having an experience like yours. Sorry for that, and thank you for pointing out this problem.",{},,User,False
