3671,IssueCommentEvent,2017-02-28 09:33:19+00:00,65724446,psycofdj/coverxygen,1496191,psycofdj,,,201057543,282989128,"I guess the problem comes from --prefix option.

This option tells converxygen to keep only files that matches given path. Default is ``/``.
Depending how you generated your documentation with doxygen, xml files may contain relative paths, stating with ``./``. If it is the case, every files will be ignored.

In version 1.2.0 I added ``--src-dir`` option which tell coverxygen what is your base directory for relative files found in doxygen's xml files.

With version 1.2.0, and assuming your source base directory is ``<path>``, try the following command :

``python3 -m coverxygen --xml-dir ./doc/xml --src-dir <path> --output doc-coverage.info``",{},,User,False
