4194,IssueCommentEvent,2017-03-12 15:26:29+00:00,51709269,mapleoin/undecorated,35473,mapleoin,,,211323925,285951925,"Hey, so I looked at this, but it seems to rely on the ordering of the elements cell_contents which varies across python versions.

The callback is actually closed over in the `wrapper` function, which makes it indistinguishable from a decorator which doesn't use [update_wrapper](https://docs.python.org/library/functools.html#functools.update_wrapper). I'm now thinking about dropping support for decorators which do not use `update_wrapper` or at least moving them to a separate function. That would have to be done in a MAJOR version of course.

I don't see a way of supporting both closures over functions and decorators without `update_wrapper`. They are basically the same thing, but should be treated differently by `undecorated`.

I'd be interested to hear your thoughts.",{},,User,False
