5410,IssueCommentEvent,2017-04-25 17:39:52+00:00,53352663,ecederstrand/exchangelib,559151,ecederstrand,,,223918161,297108518,"200B is definitely wrong. Maybe you're not fully reading the file content, or maybe your Excel file is mangled?

I just wrote this little example that works for me (exhcangelib==1.9.2 against Office365). I can open the Excel sheet via the web client just fine:

```python
c = Credentials(username, password)
a = Account(primary_smtp_address=c.username, credentials=c, autodiscover=True)

with open('sheet.xlsx', 'rb') as f:
    content = f.read()  # Read the binary file contents
att = FileAttachment(name='sheet.xlsx', content=content)
m = Message(account=a, folder=a.inbox, subject='Excel attachment')
m.attach(att)
m.save()

m.refresh()  # Get updated item from server
for a in m.attachments:
    print(a)  # Just print the attachment to see all the attributes
# m.delete()
```",{},,User,False
