5433,IssueCommentEvent,2015-11-10 23:10:01+00:00,695611,etianen/django-reversion,489057,tdruez,,,99490015,155597084,"So after looking deeper into my problem, I realized that the issue is not about the comparison logic of `save_revision()`, but rather about the `ignore_duplicates` value passed to `save_revision()`.

`ignore_duplicates` in `save_revision()` is always `False`, even if `ignore_duplicate_revisions = True` is set on the ModelAdmin.

It actually comes back to my original comment from https://github.com/etianen/django-reversion/issues/442#issue-99490015
> The value of the variable is not given to the revision manager anymore

At https://github.com/etianen/django-reversion/blob/master/src/reversion/revisions.py#L188
`_stack` contains 2 RevisionContextStackFrame objects, the first one has `ignore_duplicates=False`,
the second one `ignore_duplicates=True`.

The second one (proper value) is poped and when we reach https://github.com/etianen/django-reversion/blob/master/src/reversion/revisions.py#L206 ,
`stack_frame.ignore_duplicates` value is `False`.

@etianen let me know what you think, I'm not sure why we end up with ignore_duplicates as False in the save logic. This is a blocker for me to upgrade to reversion 1.9.x, that's required to upgrade Django to 1.9.x as well, as reversion 1.8.x is not compatible.
Thanks.",{},,User,False
