6010,IssueCommentEvent,2016-09-26 14:15:04+00:00,13231340,kennethreitz/flask-sockets,904705,oblalex,,,179081199,249581619,"Well, `Initializing WebSocket` message comes from [gevent-websocket](https://bitbucket.org/noppo/gevent-websocket/src/e366791ba8793ff7df8e0a80939092f77fe4667b/geventwebsocket/handler.py?at=0.9.5&fileviewer=file-view-default#handler.py-69).

Due to code, [it is expected to see](https://bitbucket.org/noppo/gevent-websocket/src/e366791ba8793ff7df8e0a80939092f77fe4667b/geventwebsocket/handler.py?at=0.9.5&fileviewer=file-view-default#handler.py-101) `Validating WebSocket request` message immediately after `Initializing WebSocket`.

However, your log contains a _part_ of traceback interweaved between those messages. This is very suspicious:

1. seems like there are simultaneous requests to your service;
2. take a look at `'wsgi.websocket_version': '13'} failed with TypeError`: there's something wrong in your WS endpoint;

I also have [a service deployed to Heroku](https://github.com/IL2HorusTeam/demo-services) which has both [HTTP endpoints](https://github.com/IL2HorusTeam/demo-services/blob/785d2b62d58d4aa910ff3196b9626b6f2824af32/project/api/services/difficulty/views.py) and [WS endpoints](https://github.com/IL2HorusTeam/demo-services/blob/785d2b62d58d4aa910ff3196b9626b6f2824af32/project/api/services/events_parser/views.py).  I make POST requests before and after connecting to WS and there is nothing similar to your messages:

```
