6261,IssueCommentEvent,2015-12-01 16:43:01+00:00,11240449,jrief/django-admin-sortable2,13573675,max-pfeiffer,,,93994828,161026448,;-)  jQuery JavaScript Library v1.11.2,{},,User,False
6262,IssueCommentEvent,2017-07-23 21:52:40+00:00,11240449,jrief/django-admin-sortable2,615759,mkoistinen,,,244812734,317284819,"Just set `actions = None` or `actions = []` on your Model's admin class.

In the project I'm working on right now, we disabled deleting objects in the admin by default. In most cases, this was the only action available. When Django (1.11+ at least) has no actions, it doesn't even bother rendering the checkboxes in the first column. It was these checkboxes that the JS in DAS2 relied upon to get the object's id/pk needed to update the currently displayed changelist to match the most recent drag operation.

Without the checkboxes, the first drag operation would work fine, but all subsequent ones jumbled up the list on the backend, making it unusable for multiple operations.

With this change, DAS2's JS gets the objects id/pk from its own widget, there-by avoiding dependency on an unrelated Django feature.

Thanks for the quick review/merge!",{},,User,False
