6361,IssueCommentEvent,2015-04-08 14:21:45+00:00,3583594,lambdalisue/django-permission,546312,lambdalisue,,,66850590,90930965,"We usually use `<app_label>.<verb>_<model>` while django follow this rule and that's why project newbies can guess the role of the permission from its name. And if you add any extra `add_comment` for other models (like `blogs.add_comment`), it is quite difficult to find which application use the permission (blogs app does not add a comment, comments app add a comment to a blog), thus I recommend you to follow the django's rule.
