6555,IssueCommentEvent,2015-09-27 15:42:55+00:00,26403639,ionelmc/python-lazy-object-proxy,129501,ionelmc,,,108541965,143569319,"Doing something special in constructor (`__new__`) only makes sense if you want subclasses to have this behavior. Do you really need that?

Otherwise just use a class decorator:
```python
def lazy(klass):
  def lazy_class(*args, **kwargs):
    return Proxy(lambda: klass(*args, **kwargs))
  lazy_class.__name__ = ""lazy_"" + klass.__name__
  return lazy_class

@lazy
class A(object):
  ....
```
",{},,User,False
