6915,IssueCommentEvent,2015-12-17 14:23:57+00:00,41557383,cloudant/python-cloudant,8793303,alfinkel,44642,cloudant,122628226,165464325,"Yep.  That is a bug for sure.  The group_level is mis-typed in our result module ARG_TYPES.  It should be set to `(int, types.NoneType)` but is currently set to `basestring`.  We'll get that in the queue to fix.

BTW, your call to `.get_view_result(...)['rows'][0]` won't ever work because that method returns a `Result` which provides you with a pythonic way of slicing and iterating through the results.  It processes the ['rows'] part automatically.  So adding it again in your code will likely cause an error or at the very least to not return anything.  Either remove the `['rows'][0]` from your call or use the `.get_view_raw_result()` method instead which returns the raw JSON response.  

Specifically to get the first Result you would do `result[:1]`.

Take a look at the Getting Started section on using [results](http://python-cloudant.readthedocs.org/en/latest/getting_started.html#dealing-with-results) for more detail and the [Result](http://python-cloudant.readthedocs.org/en/latest/result.html) section also has some good examples.",{},,User,False
