8702,IssueCommentEvent,2018-04-05 18:11:55+00:00,79510167,pypa/pipenv,355454,Flimm,647025,pypa,261910932,379027938,"@uranusjr I read all of https://docs.pipenv.org and https://docs.pipenv.org/basics/ , and unless I missed it, it never mentions where the `virtualenv` directories are installed, nor does it warn anybody that renaming or moving the project directory will cause the `virtualenv` directory to have to be recreated.

`PIPENV_VENV_IN_PROJECT` is confusingly named, since `pipenv` does not use [`venv`](https://docs.python.org/3/library/venv.html) shipped in the standard library, it uses `virtualenv`, which is a different project.

