8870,IssueCommentEvent,2016-08-18 11:12:05+00:00,318058,twisted/txmongo,909638,IlyaSkriblovsky,716546,twisted,171259928,240693564,"> Every timer tick is what? Default ping interval (10s)?
Yes, `ping_interval=10`. But timing defaults are the subject of discussion, of course

Every `ping_interval` we open new connection (not in pool) to *each* distinct address of server nodes we are connected too (because with `slave_ok=True` connections in the pool might be to different nodes). In these new connections we send `ismaster` and if we received any answer within `ping_timeout` seconds, we consider this server address alive. If the procedure fails for any address, we are forcibly closing all connections in the pool that are connected to *this* address.",{},,User,False
