9039,IssueCommentEvent,2015-04-29 15:29:08+00:00,2640766,astropy/photutils,852409,cdeil,847984,astropy,67014484,97470985,"We have a ""future"" milestone in photutils (and I think it exists in Astropy, too).

The difference wrt. no milestone set is small.
A new issue or PR that comes in has no milestone set.
Then one of the maintainers looks at it and sets a milestone.
So having a ""future"" milestone helps a bit to make sure important issues aren't forgotten because no-one set a milestone.

I think it's a bit useful, but I'm also not opposed to removing the future milestone if others think it's complicated.
",{},,User,False
