9143,IssueCommentEvent,2015-07-11 03:34:08+00:00,2014929,scikit-image/scikit-image,2184487,JDWarner,897180,scikit-image,94428469,120566690,"Proof:

``` python
from skimage.filters import gaussian_filter
from skimage.data import camera

# Original cameraman
cam0 = camera().astype(float)

# Apply gaussian filter with negative `sigma`
cam1 = gaussian_filter(cam0, sigma=-0.7)
cam2 = gaussian_filter(cam0, sigma=-5)

# Plot the original and difference images
fig, (ax0, ax1, ax2) = plt.subplots(ncols=3, figsize=(10, 6))

ax0.imshow(cam0, cmap='gray', interpolation='nearest')
ax1.imshow(cam0 - cam1, cmap='gray', interpolation='nearest')
ax2.imshow(cam0 - cam2, cmap='gray', interpolation='nearest')
plt.show()

# Quantitative tests
np.testing.assert_allclose(np.zeros_like(cam0), cam0 - cam1)
np.testing.assert_allclose(np.zeros_like(cam0), cam0 - cam2)
```
![image](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/2184487/8632132/bd401338-2753-11e5-94a0-229431a72340.png)
",{},,User,False
