9319,IssueCommentEvent,2016-10-14 21:57:24+00:00,16366081,numenta/nupic.core,239726,scottpurdy,1039191,numenta,177963262,253929603,"People who had this problem:

- http://stackoverflow.com/questions/39552473/undefined-symbols-for-architecture-x86-64-once-i-got-xcode-8 - This seems like a common issue with XCode version changes where people have to add or remove a framework from the search path in order to get linkers working again.

XCode 8 release notes:
https://developer.apple.com/library/content/releasenotes/DeveloperTools/RN-Xcode/Introduction.html

There is something about `Enable Testability` that passes `-export_dynamic` to the linker. I tried adding this in CMake but it didn't make a difference.

Issues related to the repackaging of out combined static library:

- http://stackoverflow.com/questions/3821916/how-to-merge-two-ar-static-libraries-into-one (suggests multiple alternatives to `cmake rcs ...` and also suggests that ranlib may be useful for building the static library index) - I tried some of these things with no difference.",{},,User,False
