9333,IssueCommentEvent,2015-11-20 11:43:21+00:00,16366081,numenta/nupic.core,470969,rcrowder,1039191,numenta,115330193,158370893,"@carlkl With NuPIC only supporting python-2.7 at the moment, we're only concerned with that right now (work has been done with six etc. to try 3.5 though). Use of NumPy is a requirement, but left to the user of NuPIC as to which version they use. I've not had a chance to benchmark MKL or an OpenBLAS version yet. We're also not aware of an users requiring linear algebra aspects, so a lower priority task right now. We currently rely on Chris. Gohlke pre-built packages to ease entry to NuPIC. And are moving towards building support packages from source, so will address that in the near future. Thanks for the reply.",{},,User,False
9334,IssueCommentEvent,2015-11-19 14:38:04+00:00,16366081,numenta/nupic.core,470969,rcrowder,1039191,numenta,117387395,158075123,"@scottpurdy cc @rhyolight This change started off as a way to get the boto based python script shared  between AppVeyor and Travis. Unfortunately the decoding of secure environment variables has hampered this on AV (https://ci.appveyor.com/tools/encrypt shows where decryption takes place). So although I had partial success running boto, it looks tricky/impossible to pass in secure variables for the  AWS secret key. As such I've reverted back to standard S3 deployment. And am hoping these changes   will get deployment working again.
requirements.txt change for numpy is to cope with the version we currently use/need on Windows. I'll check why 1.9.2 has been forced..

I moved the boto script to the /ci directory. Should this be moved back to /ci/travis ? If not, then this is ready for review.
",{},,User,False
9339,IssueCommentEvent,2015-02-10 10:27:26+00:00,16366081,numenta/nupic.core,3386273,david-ragazzi,1039191,numenta,52647670,73677057,"@rhyolight @rcrowder

I think that some updates are need for this super issue:
- Although worthwhile, `inline asm support for x64 builds` (https://github.com/numenta/nupic.core/issues/236) is not a requirement for nupic.core build and pass on tests under Windows. So I suggested we move this issue to `0.3.0` or for a non-planned release.
- `Build artifacts implementation` (https://github.com/numenta/nupic.core/issues/311) is an explicit job of `0.3.0`.

So only `ensure Cap'n Proto doesn't break Windows builds` (https://github.com/numenta/nupic.core/issues/321) is an requirement for build and tests pass under Windows. So it remains in `0.2.0`.

",{},,User,False
