9381,IssueCommentEvent,2015-04-22 17:47:37+00:00,2562442,mozilla-services/cornice,686587,aguereca,1066228,mozilla-services,69961320,95281234,"Thanks for all your feedback, each have bring a piece of truth to this, so I've make a few new tests and effectively the problem is that I had defined the same route for path and collection_path, my oversight mainly because both are required and before 1.0.0 if the class defining the resource didn't have a method for that path then was simply ignored.
For completeness, previous pseudo example is fixed by this update:

``` python
from cornice.resource import resource, view

@resource(collection_path='/user/{user_id}/follow', path='/user/{user_id}/follow/{id}')
class UserFollowViews(object):
    ...
    @view(validators=(validate_authentication, validate_user))
    def post(self):
    ....


@resource(collection_path='/user/{user_id}/following', path='/user/{user_id}/following/{id}')
class UserFollowingViews(object):
    ...
    @view(validators=(validate_authentication, validate_user))
    def collection_get(self):
    ....
```

The warning implemented by @circlingthesun will be very helpful for anybody else upgrading to 1.0.0 on same situation. I'll actually recommend adding it into the list of breaking changes of 1.0.0, because upgrading effectively breaks routing on incorrectly defined resources.",{},,User,False
