10111,IssueCommentEvent,2017-03-29 17:06:30+00:00,3510804,GalSim-developers/GalSim,623887,rmjarvis,1462196,GalSim-developers,112910573,290156468,"I just changed the wcs in CRG to use the minimum of the two stepk values, and the only thing that broke was the round trip test that is dominated by ringing.  The ringing seems to have increased a bit, so it only passes if 5% -> 8% in one of the tests (6% in the other).  I'm not very able to evaluate whether this is actually a problem or not.

cf. ebaf707

The running time for all `test_crg` functions in test_real.py went from 1:35 -> 1:39, which seems relatively negligible to me.  

Profiling indicates that `np.lstsq` is indeed the tall pole at 40 sec (from 38 previously).  I believe I can pretty massively speed that up with a call to the C++ layer to use tmv instead of numpy.  Plus, probably SVD is unnecessary, and we can use QRP which is much faster.

TL;DR I'd prefer to switch back to having drawKImage and InterpolatedKImage only taking a scale, not a more general wcs.",{},,User,False
10112,IssueCommentEvent,2015-12-29 14:48:52+00:00,3510804,GalSim-developers/GalSim,1454906,rmandelb,1462196,GalSim-developers,118275516,167803316,"OK.  If we want to do this in generic a way as possible, then I think #308 is the way to go.

Are you willing to / interested in implementing #308, and I will (a) put together a routine that uses that functionality to construct a resolution factor, and (b) work on the yaml file?",{},,User,False
10115,IssueCommentEvent,2017-03-29 15:52:13+00:00,3510804,GalSim-developers/GalSim,3650485,jmeyers314,1462196,GalSim-developers,112910573,290134531,">Could you explain why you decided that was necessary?

Sure.  I think it was mostly because I forgot that that's what RealGalaxy did.  That said, I believe the slow part of CRG is solving the weighted linear least squares problem for each Fourier mode.  So reducing the number of modes will, I think, be a non-negligible speed up for what's a pretty slow bit of code.  If you'd like to hide the wcs stuff from the user (`_wcs` kwarg?) and just make it an implementation detail of CRG, though, that's fine with me.",{},,User,False
