10160,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-17 16:06:58+00:00,89010314,domoinc/domo-python-sdk,4968324,yunruiwatts,1482178,domoinc,266138175,337281923,"@ldacey I personally haven't used workbench, so I'm not sure what that approach actually does. Are you wanting to know how to append to a dataset using the API, or wanting to know how to append in a particular way?

As for upsert, we do have the capability to have upsert datasets, but they have to be enabled in your instance. There are some caveats to using them, though - you can't do an upsert operation, you update the schema of the dataset to specify one or more columns that will be used to determine if a new row should replace an existing row. Once the schema has been updated, every append to the dataset is actually an upsert. Appending to an upsert dataset is not quite as fast (especially if the dataset is large), and dataflows built on an upsert dataset can take two to three times as long to update because it has to wait for the upsert to be evaluated instead of being able to just use the newly-appended data.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
