10538,IssueCommentEvent,2017-02-17 11:40:25+00:00,51875828,python/typed_ast,245905,ddfisher,1525981,python,208232424,280628186,"This is expected -- typed_ast made some backwards incompatible changes when updating to 1.0.

To fix, use **mypy** (no longer **mypy-lang**) version 0.471, which has an upper bound on the typed-ast version it installs.  The next release of mypy will be out in a couple weeks and will be updated to work with typed-ast 1.0.",{},,User,False
10539,IssueCommentEvent,2018-05-08 23:03:04+00:00,51875828,python/typed_ast,245905,ddfisher,1525981,python,318680722,387569429,"Thanks for the PR, @ethanhs!  My preference would be to wait on merging this until the PR to cpython is merged, or maybe even until we pick it up naturally by tracking cpython ast (depending on how far off that will be).  If we want to merge this before we get it naturally by tracking ast, we also need to update the [development philosophy section of the readme](https://github.com/python/typed_ast#development-philosophy) (to mention that sometimes we backport things from upstream ast) and the [module docstring of the ast3 module](https://github.com/python/typed_ast/blob/master/typed_ast/ast3.py#L13) to document the specific change.

That said, if this is a change that mypy is anxious to have, we could potentially bend the rules a bit here. :)",{},COLLABORATOR,User,False
