11010,IssueCommentEvent,2018-03-28 08:43:39+00:00,81349068,snipsco/snips-nlu,4267202,ClemDoum,2564618,snipsco,304266452,376808944,"For now we have no plan for Portuguese.

@gosailing @Vitorbnc if you want to use the NLU for a language we don't support yet, the main blocker is going to be the builtin entities.

For now we use `Rustling` and our [builtin entities ontology](https://github.com/snipsco/snips-nlu-ontology). These 2 tools are used in the [Rust inference](https://github.com/snipsco/snips-nlu-rs) on-device.

Now if you're not interested in the on-device part you can still bypass the ontology and use your own. There are some other tools that you can use for builtin entities such as [duckling](https://github.com/facebook/duckling/tree/master/Duckling)

- replace all imports of `from snips_nlu_ontology import x, y, z` by `from my_nlu_ontology import x, y, z` module
- reimplement the `x`, `y`, `z` function  on your side
- for instance you could use [duckling](https://github.com/facebook/duckling/tree/master/Duckling) as `BuiltinEntityParser`

If you're successful, we'll try to see how we can make the ontology module configurable, this way no one will be bound to someone else's ontology",{},COLLABORATOR,User,False
