11324,IssueCommentEvent,2016-07-06 14:43:37+00:00,11031844,uqfoundation/dill,321534,mmckerns,2855931,uqfoundation,127623702,230793869,"Just to note, in case it wasn't clear from the above… `dill` bootstrapping (i.e. `extend` on import) does work in python3.x -- however, it only affects `pickle._dump`, `pickle._dumps`, and similarly for loading.  In 3.x, these functions replace `dump`, `dumps`, etc if `_pickle` (the C version) doesn't work for some reason.  The functions `dump` and friends come from `pickle._Pickler`, which **is extended** by `dill` in python3.x.  What is currently not done, is copying the dispatch table from the `_Pickler` into the `Pickler`… which would be the equivalent of copying the dispatch table from `pickle` to `cPickle` in python2.x.",{},,User,False
