11383,IssueCommentEvent,2017-07-12 00:31:54+00:00,43620042,AzureAD/azure-activedirectory-library-for-python,6620414,danieldobalian,2966316,AzureAD,224548820,314610108,"@patchie you make a good point, I did not include the true getting started tutorial.  We definitely have something for the first experience when using this stuff at [the v2.0 App Registration Portal](https://apps.dev.microsoft.com).  All you need to do is sign in, create a new app, and select ""Help me get started"". This will drop you into a guided walkthrough of what's going on.  

This is a newer experience so there's limited language support, so if you need Python we have a [Flask code sample](https://github.com/Azure-Samples/active-directory-python-flask-graphapi-web-v2) that is really simple and will help you write a tiny app that signs someone in and calls the Microsoft Graph. Hoping to add Python to that experience shortly. 

The one important caveat is this is the Azure AD v2.0 endpoint whereas ADAL is the authentication library built for the v1 endpoint. I'm recommending this as ADAL and v1.0 don't have a super simple experience that I think you're looking for.  Depending on your scenario, I would recommend going through this experience to get a lay-of-the-land, then jump into one of the more involved code samples that are going to be closer to the production app you want to build. ",{},,User,False
