11584,IssueCommentEvent,2016-03-11 20:28:26+00:00,7137821,cloudtools/troposphere,389478,nickmoorman,3028687,cloudtools,140044927,195536918,"While we're on the subject, I just discovered another validation that could be added.  The top-level mapping keys (such as `v1.1.8-coreos.0` in my latest comment) apparently have undocumented requirements:

    A client error (ValidationError) occurred when calling the CreateStack operation:
        Template format error: Mappings element name 'v1.1.8_coreos.0' must be non-empty and can contain only alphanumerics, '-' or '.'

I believe that would make the final validation requirements for a mapping something like:

    {
        ""([A-Za-z0-9]|-|\.)+"": {
            ""([A-Za-z0-9])*"": ""No known requirements?""
        }
    }",{},,User,False
