11590,IssueCommentEvent,2016-05-10 19:38:41+00:00,22072746,pantsbuild/pex,1883523,kwlzn,3065172,pantsbuild,153996159,218267180,"any clue what pex release you're on? I'd halfway expect this to work based on: https://github.com/pantsbuild/pex/commit/0b1e5fdd1b6f33bd7ab1828c986c40e384dbb9e9

but I've also heard recent anecdotal stories that it does not work against wheels generated by the `manylinux` docker image (which also use the `cp27mu` abi tag - `m` denotes with 'pymalloc' support and `u` denotes wide unicode). have not yet dug in, but we'll also need this soon. if you guys have cycles, I'd be happy to review any PRs or otherwise will plan to dig into this myself sometime in the next few weeks.",{},,User,False
11591,IssueCommentEvent,2018-05-24 17:43:18+00:00,22072746,pantsbuild/pex,3359631,DrumMachineLearning,3065172,pantsbuild,325231646,391800657,"I think I may be experiencing a similar issue, although I'm using pants. I've opened a [pants issue](https://github.com/pantsbuild/pants/issues/5862) and have a small, self-contained [example](https://github.com/DrumMachineLearning/pants_build_example) with debug output.

Apologies if I shouldn't be cross-posting here; the pantsbuild.slack.com folks thought it may be an ABI issue so I figured it was relevant.

This works fine if I build a wheel out of my package, add it to `/wheelhouse` and `requirements.txt` and then run `pex -f wheelhouse --no-build --platform=linux-x86_64-cp-27-mu --platform=macosx-10.13-x86_64 -r requirements.txt -o my_pex.pex -m my_entry_point:main` but it would be great to continue using pants and avoiding to have to pre-build the wheel.

