11673,IssueCommentEvent,2015-04-14 01:43:00+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,157586,jsirois,3065172,pantsbuild,68232064,92555718,"Flipping to your side for a second - your scheme would really need to write this out to a file so the ng server stayed up and each pants run knew the list of things in the ng.  Flipping back - I'm not in favor since this still does not address rebooting subnails w/o taking down the ng server, nor does it support dropping subnails.  You can do both with classlaoder per each and that allows for all sorts of control.",{},,User,False
11676,IssueCommentEvent,2016-10-24 18:07:44+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,157586,jsirois,3065172,pantsbuild,184909373,255819115,"OK - I was being lazy there to see if there was a default.
In the pants repo you get:
```
$ ./pants options | grep scalastyle | grep config
compile.scalastyle.config = /home/jsirois/dev/pantsbuild/pants/build-support/scalastyle/scalastyle_config.xml (from CONFIG in pants.ini)
```

The visual hints in that output are lost here, but `compile.scalastyle` is blue - that's the option's ""scope"" (a namespace), and the `config` part is yellow, that's the simple option name. You can set options for the repo as a whole using `pants.ini` with an entry like
```ini
[scope]
name: value
```

So, in this case:
```ini
[compile.scalastyle]
config: a/path/here
```",{},,User,False
