11700,IssueCommentEvent,2018-05-30 16:25:36+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,157586,jsirois,3065172,pantsbuild,327796710,393225865,"Noting that one fix is to kill the environment marker in our requirements.txt. IIRC this was added pre-emptively by Benjy for consumers of pants as a python3 library. Since pants does not support running under python3 today, I can't imagine it can be used as a python3 library today, except by luck use of just the right subset of imports that happens to be python3 compatible.",{},MEMBER,User,False
11704,IssueCommentEvent,2016-09-01 20:29:05+00:00,7209075,pantsbuild/pants,1883523,kwlzn,3065172,pantsbuild,174583686,244202047,"ah yes - in that case, there is a ~known resolve caching behavior issue (#3527) which is further exacerbated by the default resolver cache ttl being set to 10 years.

this is controlled by the `--python-setup-resolver-cache-ttl` flag - for topical relief from stale resolves, you can adjust this to something closer to an hour in your `pants.ini` which will cause the resolver cache to invalidate more frequently than 10 years (with a tradeoff of more frequent fetches, which will usually happen anyway between `clean-all`).

if you encounter another repro, you can also try passing `--python-setup-resolver-cache-ttl=0` to verify this is indeed the issue that you're hitting.",{},,User,False
