11723,IssueCommentEvent,2018-07-04 05:20:12+00:00,93721432,awslabs/sockeye,455256,mjpost,3299148,awslabs,337745585,402366103,"I think we do have something close to a formal API. The preferred approach is to construct [inference.TranslatorInput](https://github.com/awslabs/sockeye/blob/3df3e50be89793a416de8111003da1473a0685bb/sockeye/inference.py#L569) objects, which are then passed to [Translator.translate()](https://github.com/awslabs/sockeye/blob/3df3e50be89793a416de8111003da1473a0685bb/sockeye/inference.py#L1070), which will translate a list of such objects as a batch. There are a handful of convenience functions for building these objects from [plain text](https://github.com/awslabs/sockeye/blob/3df3e50be89793a416de8111003da1473a0685bb/sockeye/inference.py#L660), from [tab-delimited input](https://github.com/awslabs/sockeye/blob/3df3e50be89793a416de8111003da1473a0685bb/sockeye/inference.py#L706) (for source factors), and from [JSON strings](https://github.com/awslabs/sockeye/blob/3df3e50be89793a416de8111003da1473a0685bb/sockeye/inference.py#L671). You can see how this is done in [translate.py](https://github.com/awslabs/sockeye/blob/master/sockeye/translate.py), the command-line API.",{},COLLABORATOR,User,False
