11730,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-12 15:55:20+00:00,93721432,awslabs/sockeye,636653,mjdenkowski,3299148,awslabs,264983171,336181902,"Great update!  My main suggestion would be to make this a CLI option until we run more experiments and also look at resetting the optimizer state for consistency.

For at least one other toolkit, Graham's [XNMT](https://github.com/neulab/xnmt), the default decay operation is rolling back parameters *and* completely resetting optimizer state (effectively starting a new training run).  We can also experiment with rolling back the optimizer state with a little more bookkeeping.

We could add add optimizer reset support in another update, test the various combinations, and have a CLI option for vanilla decay vs smart rollback.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
