12200,IssueCommentEvent,2017-02-08 22:01:58+00:00,53143022,oduwsdl/ipwb,2514780,machawk1,4416806,oduwsdl,139708072,278476082,"Part of the issue here is path resolution. A request from `http://127.0.0.1:5000/http://domain/~myHomepage` for `http://127.0.0.1:5000/http://domain/~myHomepage/me.jpg` requests `http://127.0.0.1:5000/me.jpg` if specified with a relative path in the archived page. #88 will help with this but pages in IPWB have to first resolve to requesting the right path if relative. #88 refers more to requesting absolute path resources, intercepting them, and pointing to the local archive as the source of the resource representation.",{},,User,False
