12585,IssueCommentEvent,2018-03-10 00:37:36+00:00,2113510,crossbario/autobahn-python,145599,meejah,5656948,crossbario,303744982,371984574,"I think the current draft-spec used SHA256 as well. We should decide on ""wamp-scram-*"" vs. ""wamp-scram"" and an ""algorithm"" param.

There's the ""authextra"" vs. not thing, but I'm currently making it work with explicit attributes in `message.Welcome` etc instead of authextra (so we could be clear on that in the 135 discussion).

The actual SCRAM RFC announces support for channel-binding via the algorithm name, too, by adding `-plus` on the end.  So probably we should say ""all WAMP SCRAM authentication methods start with `wamp-scram-` and the rest of the string is the algorithm name""",{},MEMBER,User,False
