12603,IssueCommentEvent,2018-02-18 18:18:24+00:00,91356408,allenai/allennlp,3291951,matt-gardner,5667695,allenai,298063793,366535560,"It'd be sad, I think, to duplicate the whole `model` block of the config file - that's just asking for trouble.  We need to take the model archive, and we really should just load the model from there, using the saved parameters.

I kind of think we'll want to allow config files, because there's a lot you could tweak.  But it'd also be nice to just have a really simple, ""take my model and fine-tune it exactly as before but on this new data"", without needing a whole new config file, with slightly different parameters.  I finished doing it just with a few flags, and will open a PR for this in a minute; my vote is to let people try this out and find out from users how we should change it.",{},MEMBER,User,False
12614,IssueCommentEvent,2018-06-17 19:18:06+00:00,91356408,allenai/allennlp,6934216,janLuke,5667695,allenai,331950029,397900126,"I made other changes in https://github.com/janLuke/allennlp/tree/embeddings_text_file. Nothing substantial.
The biggest one is probably that I removed ``self._buffer`` and added a ``self._iterator``:
```
        if self._num_tokens:
            self._iterator = self._handle
        else:
            self._iterator = itertools.chain([first_line], self._handle)
```
I think it simplifies the code. Methods become one-liners.
",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
