12794,IssueCommentEvent,2015-04-17 21:45:43+00:00,11589713,deis/deis,1821014,krancour,6117407,deis,53052185,94081520,"@Blystad as @bacongobbler pointed out, `deis logs` won't work if an operator opts out of the storage subsystem.  I think we knew this going in.  What would you think about this... what if as part of the installer I am working on, if the operator opts out of the storage subsystem, besides asking them where to drain logs _to_, I also ask them for a URL where devs can access those logs?  I can stored that in etcd.  _Then_ you can write code in `deis-cotnroller` (if you're going to already be in there anyway) that recovers from `deis logs` failure (due to missing volume/folder) by displaying a URL where they can find logs (or optionally popping open their browser for them).

Example:

```
$ deis logs

Since the Deis storage subsystem is not installed, application logs are drained to an external log server only.

Your system administrator says these logs are accessible at the following location:

