13037,IssueCommentEvent,2015-10-29 15:35:51+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,2797735,mcg1969,6392739,conda,114060495,152217860,"When implementing my pruning pass I was tempted to refactor the VersionSpec object a bit. The result would allow for build numbers in inequalities as well as more flexible ""or"" constraints. I'm pretty sure the parsing pass will have to be careful here. For instance, I don't think `>= 0.1.2-3` will work, because the splits happen on whitespace. (After all, what if some package with a weird version convention uses a dash?) So it might have to be `>= 0.1.2 3`, as non-intuitive as that may seem.",{},,User,False
13038,IssueCommentEvent,2016-07-17 21:05:20+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,327925,takluyver,6392739,conda,165942681,233204068,"We also have a very vague plan to integrate a notion of environments into the default kernelspec system. We postponed this because:

1. It's not clear what model to use - there can be multiple kernels available in one environment, multiple environments available with the same type of kernel, and kernels that don't really match a specific environment.
2. We want this to be generic for different environment systems. Just for Python there's conda, virtualenv and pyenv, and no doubt other languages have their own similar tools. It's also not clear where the line is - do we try to handle docker containers as part of this too?

This hasn't got any less challenging, but if Anaconda feels the need to push environments into the existing kernelspec mechanism, maybe we need to try to work these issues out and produce a more general mechanism.",{},,User,False
13041,IssueCommentEvent,2015-09-11 19:24:07+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,71486,asmeurer,6392739,conda,106074629,139638586,"conda only uses the channel information for that given command to find packages, so local packages won't be kept unless a channel with them is in the condarc or provided with `-c` flags. ",{},,User,False
13042,IssueCommentEvent,2017-10-04 13:32:12+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,2746263,gwvr,6392739,conda,97297498,334156000,"`conda update --all`
Updates the packages within a miniconda environment. I've used this repeatedly over the months since I installed miniconda, but eventually hit the following error:
`Installing conda-forge::pyasn1-0.3.6-py_0 requires a minimum conda version of 4.3.`

To update miniconda itself, download the latest installer and run it with the upgrade option.
On linux:
```bash
bash Miniconda3-latest-Linux-x86_64.sh -u
```",{},NONE,User,False
