13073,IssueCommentEvent,2017-03-14 13:00:21+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,1672353,wulmer,6392739,conda,211449963,286413380,"I am having the same issue with conda 4.3.13. This problem currently blocks our Jenkins builds on Windows... :-(
It seems that if there is a problem while creating an environment, conda retries again and again. (Each of the failed processes spawns a new subprocess which also fails and which also starts a new subprocess and so on...)

I was able to get the command line of the spawned Python processes. It always reads the same:

    ""C:\Program Files\Anaconda3\pythonw.exe"" ""-c"" ""import menuinst; menuinst.install('c:\\Jenkins\\WORKSP~1\\XQ_MUL~1\\FED2B2~1\\virtual-env2\\Menu\\spyder_shortcut.json', False, 'c:\\Jenkins\\WORKSP~1\\XQ_MUL~1\\FED2B2~1\\virtual-env2')""

As I don't run with admin rights (and AFAIK creating start menu shortcuts with conda shows a UAC prompt) I assume that my background Jenkins process tries to get a UAC approval but can't as it is running in the background. So somehow conda tries it again over and over...

I will try to change my env setup commands to skip menu shortcut creation... hope this avoids the issue...

My conda install is:

               platform : win-64
          conda version : 4.3.13
       conda is private : False
      conda-env version : 4.3.13
    conda-build version : 2.1.5
         python version : 3.6.0.final.0
       requests version : 2.13.0
       root environment : C:\Program Files\Anaconda3  (read only)
    default environment : C:\Program Files\Anaconda3",{},,User,False
