13086,IssueCommentEvent,2017-09-26 18:41:02+00:00,6235174,conda/conda,7903078,tylerjereddy,6392739,conda,260693546,332295537,"Ah, you are correct. This has [previously generated confusion for users](https://github.com/conda/conda/issues/448), and the conclusion there seems to be that the conda team is not interested in excluding site directories entirely (for understandable reasons -- this changes the default behavior of Python).

I'm closing this because there are various ways to achieve what we need for our project -- i.e.,
`export PYTHONNOUSERSITE=True` will apparently give us the kind of environment isolation (no site packages whatsoever in a conda env) that is desired, as suggested by one of my colleagues in the above linked issue.",{},NONE,User,False
