13306,IssueCommentEvent,2018-06-12 04:00:39+00:00,97101009,elastic/apm-agent-python,4790,karmi,6764390,elastic,330977325,396458624,"@bastbnl, the [list of commits](https://github.com/elastic/apm-agent-python/pull/226/commits) indicates that you've used two different email addresses in Git, so that would need to be fixed in order for our automatic checks to work... 

I haven't checked the patch content — please follow @beniwohli's suggestions here —, but it seems like the list of commits can be squashed into one, since it's one logical change.

Therefore, please set the [name](https://help.github.com/articles/setting-your-username-in-git/) and [email](https://help.github.com/articles/setting-your-commit-email-address-in-git/) in Git, and run the [interactive rebase](https://help.github.com/articles/about-git-rebase/) on your branch to create a single commit.

Afterwards, use the `git commit --verbose --amend --reset-author` command in terminal, to pick up any new Git configurations for name/email.

The only last step is to: `git push --force`, when the branch is pointed to your origin correctly (""bastbnl:bastbnl-patch-225"").


",{},MEMBER,User,False
