13528,IssueCommentEvent,2015-12-02 19:30:03+00:00,4127088,Azure/azure-sdk-for-python,1696845,huguesv,6844498,Azure,118433104,161407088,"It could be that the service principal doesn't have permissions for Windows Azure Service Management.  It's harder to find info on using oauth with ASM because most users just used certificates which are much simpler.  Most of the docs on it are targeting ARM.

I setup my subscription for testing the SDK several months ago, and it works for both ASM and ARM.  It took a long time to get it working, and I haven't touched it since.

I am using username/password.  Note that this is user under a Microsoft Azure Active Directory, not a Microsoft account such as username@oulook.com.

From memory/looking at my subscription:

In the (old) portal active directory, i selected my active directory.  I don't know if you get one by default or if you need to create one.

I added a new user under that active directory named 'user'

In the 'user' configuration page, under role, organization role, I've selected Global Admin

Allow the user to sign in and access services : allow

Then I set user@ptvsazureoutlook.onmicrosoft.com as a co-administrator in the portal settings/administrators page.

In the tests, I call the ADAL helper I mentioned above.

def get_token():
    return get_token_from_username_password(
        'https://login.microsoftonline.com/d6509e0c-ca64-4e5d-0000-90a5b7d279e8/',
        'user@ptvsazureoutlook.onmicrosoft.com',
        '<password censored>',
    )

As far as to finding out what GUID to use in that first parameter, the one place I'm able to see it in the portal isn't under users, but under applications.  It's the same for all web applications.  You select one and click on VIEW ENDPOINTS in the bottom toolbar.  If you don't have any web application, I guess you can add one temporarily, look at its endpoints and then delete it.


We have a new developer working on the SDK starting next week that will go through this, and we'll make sure that one of the first tasks is to produce a doc that explains how to set AAD for testing.

Meanwhile, if you prefer to not spend any more time on oauth for now, we can take care of generating the recording file that's necessary for the test to pass.

",{},,User,False
