13975,IssueCommentEvent,2018-01-04 03:23:41+00:00,33653601,jupyter/notebook,22313470,avriLee,7388996,jupyter,285626805,355190113,"em,i tried it and found if we follow as i mentioned above, Comm is unnecessary, _while **customizing the execution**_ of codes in kernel is the key. here's my personal 'solution':
- _step 1:_ prepare the template js file( use placeholder e.g. {code} ):
```Javascript
require([
    'services/kernels/kernel'
], function(kernel) {
    kernel.Kernel.prototype._execute = kernel.Kernel.prototype.execute;
    kernel.Kernel.prototype.execute = function (code, callbacks, options) {
        // var str = 'foo = 0\n';
        var str = '{code}';
        code = str + code;
        return this._execute(code, callbacks, options);
    };
});
```
- _step 2:_ when triggered( e.g. clicking the button ), modify the template file
- _step 3:_ trigger batch operation i.e. install & enable in nbextension
- _output:_ worked as expected!_( Aha, it seems like the super man )_
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/22313470/34549088-081f60ac-f141-11e7-994a-34f726cb0ebe.png)

_**So**_, it may evolve into: 
  **is there any public or recommended way to customize the execution?**",{},NONE,User,False
