14143,IssueCommentEvent,2017-12-21 18:46:54+00:00,52009226,Duke-GCB/DukeDSClient,2752599,dleehr,7875151,Duke-GCB,282141708,353427079,"I tested out this branch with a [Jupyter Notebook](https://github.com/dleehr/notebooks/blob/master/dukedsclient-sdk-exploration.ipynb)

Some feedback, summarized from today's call

- The focus on file operations is good, we likely don't need things like granting access or searching provenance for the intended audience
- I think the usability can be further streamlined. Having a dead-simple interface like [requests](http://requests.readthedocs.io/en/master/) would be more approachable than the current object-oriented implementation. For example:
```
import DukeDS
DukeDS.download_file('Project A', '/raw/sample1.fa')
filenames = DukeDS.list_files('Project A')
for filename in filenames:
  if '.md5' in filename:
    DukeDS.download_file('Project A', filename)
```
- Default to common, expected behaviors (e.g. download and upload assume the same target file name but may allow user to override with a named parameter)
- Default to referencing resources by name (project, file, folder) rather than ID. When a conflict arises, fail with instructions on how to reference the resource by ID. Though this requires the client code to resolve IDs and therefore takes more time, it greatly simplifies the use and I think that's a win for this project.


",{},OWNER,User,False
