14452,IssueCommentEvent,2016-06-09 06:21:17+00:00,39923176,BD2KGenomics/toil-scripts,7576256,jvivian,8701293,BD2KGenomics,159286606,224809847,"Jenkins, test this please",{},,User,False
14453,IssueCommentEvent,2016-04-26 02:57:02+00:00,39923176,BD2KGenomics/toil-scripts,7576256,jvivian,8701293,BD2KGenomics,150986883,214592636,"@hannes-ucsc Jenkins build fails due to timeout of bwa test.   On Openstack (15 cores), it runs in 7 minutes but on a 2 core m3.large the BWA algorithm is too cpu intensive to finish within 30m even for a very small input (~160M).   I looked on the Jenkins slave and can see by the tmp directory that BWA was almost finished running.  We could make the toil-scripts slave a little beefier and it should go through — I'd recommend a c3.large as the best price point at 4-cores. ",{},,User,False
14456,IssueCommentEvent,2016-01-07 08:16:20+00:00,39923176,BD2KGenomics/toil-scripts,5143256,hannes-ucsc,8701293,BD2KGenomics,124383250,169592209,"Converting the directory tree into a package tree is a good idea as it allows for code reuse. But there are a few caveats (and most of them have to do with how hot-deployment of user scripts works in Toil):

1.	It should be done as a separate PR, that gets merged quickly. Having PRs with structural changes open for a long time is a pain in wrt conflicts. Alternatively, we could just merge this PR soon.

2.	`adam_gatk_pipline` is missing `__init__.py`

3.	User scripts (or rather *user modules*) must be invoked with `python -m` followed by a fully-qualified module path, e.g.
	```
	cd src
	python -m toil_scripts.gatk_germline.germline ...
	```
	Otherwise, Toil can't figure out where the root of the tree is.
	
	This also means that wrapper shell scripts need to be changed and possibly even moved. I'll discuss with @jvivian.

4.	Toil will compile and zip all modules in the *entire* package tree (via PyZipFile). This means that a whole bunch of unused files will be sent to the cluster nodes. I think that's ok and if it turns out not to be, we can break toil-scripts up into multiple package trees.

5.	Some of the module and package names are a bit long, maybe we can remove the `_pipeline` from the end of module or package names. We could also adopt the convention of always naming user modules `toil.py` or `main.py`. The above example would then become

	```
	cd src
	python -m toil_scripts.gatk_germline.toil ...
	```
",{},,User,False
