14858,IssueCommentEvent,2016-01-19 19:40:54+00:00,26516210,letsencrypt/letsencrypt,6504915,bmw,9289019,letsencrypt,124672490,172962917,"@TimorLee, running the client outside of `virtualenv` is not officially supported, but there is nothing in the code that stops you from trying. We recommend that you use `virtualenv` because installing packages globally through `pip` can corrupt your OS.

With that said, `letsencrypt` does require a number of other packages be installed which you may not have on your system. Additionally, depending on your method of obtaining a cert, we may have to bind to port 80 or 443 which also requires root.

YMMV when using `letsencrypt` on a shared hosting provider where you don't have root access. While somewhat tedious, your best bet is to install `letsencrypt` on your desktop and use the [manual plugin](https://letsencrypt.readthedocs.org/en/latest/using.html#manual). For more help on this, check out the [community forums](https://community.letsencrypt.org/).",{},,User,False
