14902,IssueCommentEvent,2015-09-24 09:01:51+00:00,26516210,letsencrypt/letsencrypt,485278,ivanr,9289019,letsencrypt,107815377,142862353,"It's not a typo; EDH-RSA-DES-CBC3-SHA is the correct name. More recent versions of OpenSSL will accept both variants, probably because most people expect the name to start with ""DHE-"". However, older versions of OpenSSL accept only the former.
```
$ openssl version
OpenSSL 0.9.8k 25 Mar 2009
$ openssl ciphers -v DHE-RSA-DES-CBC3-SHA
Error in cipher list
5325:error:1410D0B9:SSL routines:SSL_CTX_set_cipher_list:no cipher match:ssl_lib.c:1217:
$ openssl ciphers -v EDH-RSA-DES-CBC3-SHA
EDH-RSA-DES-CBC3-SHA    SSLv3 Kx=DH       Au=RSA  Enc=3DES(168) Mac=SHA1
```
The ""EDH-"" variant is still the only variant listed in the ""openssl ciphers"" output:
```
$ openssl version
OpenSSL 1.0.2d 9 Jul 2015
$ openssl ciphers -V | grep EDH
          0x00,0x16 - EDH-RSA-DES-CBC3-SHA    SSLv3 Kx=DH       Au=RSA  Enc=3DES(168) Mac=SHA1
          0x00,0x13 - EDH-DSS-DES-CBC3-SHA    SSLv3 Kx=DH       Au=DSS  Enc=3DES(168) Mac=SHA1
          0x00,0x15 - EDH-RSA-DES-CBC-SHA     SSLv3 Kx=DH       Au=RSA  Enc=DES(56)   Mac=SHA1
          0x00,0x12 - EDH-DSS-DES-CBC-SHA     SSLv3 Kx=DH       Au=DSS  Enc=DES(56)   Mac=SHA1
```
Although it's common to separate cipher suites using colon, I prefer spaces, which make the configuration easier to read.",{},,User,False
