14991,IssueCommentEvent,2015-01-31 22:51:00+00:00,4235447,django-salesforce/django-salesforce,251738,hynekcer,9872531,django-salesforce,55907730,72340974,"I can look at it in March. I wouldn't like to write much code neither to add new requirements. I think the sooner you do it yourself. Possibilities:

* If someone has installed [beatbox](https://pypi.python.org/pypi/beatbox/) then it can be used for this. It can be written on four lines according to readme, about ten lines including auth by django-salesforce credentials.. (I used that package before django-salesforce.)
* If someone wants to install a custom APEX code from any howto existing currently on the web then it can be used by django-salesforce.

I'm undecided between them and I'm open to both yet, until know what is acceptable for other people. I think that the same one of these should be used also for our future extensions, e.g. for insert and update of multiple SF objects.

Our interface of Lead conversion should be a simple function e.g. `convert_lead(lead, to='Contact', db='salesforce')`. I don't see a suitable class, because we can't know easily where the Contact or Lead models are implemented by the user, so we can't extend them. The user can add the function to his Lead.

I think that REST api was a good idea. New functionalities are added for REST-like APIs by SFDC, not for SOAP. ",{},,User,False
