15337,IssueCommentEvent,2018-06-18 23:19:16+00:00,112676803,apple/turicreate,902935,gustavla,10639145,apple,333449616,398225026,"A bit late here since this merged, but this is what I wrote on the closed PR:

Turi Create links directly with libpng and libjpeg, and we recently changed `pixel_data` to rely on this instead of PIL. In the spirit of avoiding unnecessary PIL dependence, I think we should use our own direct linkage here as well.

We do have `write_image` in `src/image/io.cpp` to do this, so we just need to expose it appropriate (look at `_extensions.load_image` for instance). Note, there is also a potential for avoiding a decode/encode, if the requested file format is the same as the internal representation inside the SFrame.

Also, should format only be implicit in the filename? What should happen if `filename` does not end with `.png`/`.jpg`/`.jpeg`?",{},COLLABORATOR,User,False
