15721,IssueCommentEvent,2018-03-23 09:17:49+00:00,32944298,Z3Prover/z3,3085284,NikolajBjorner,11668813,Z3Prover,307555186,375590040,"Seems to a question of what defines a certificate for satisfiability. It isn't a constructive certificate in that only one possible value of b is possible in this case, but it is a certificate because the RHS has some value, and whatever value it is, becomes the value of b. In the case this isn't workable for an application, one approach is to introduce a configuration option that prevents the solve-eqs tactic from solving equalities that have right-sides with quantifiers.",{},CONTRIBUTOR,User,False
