15769,IssueCommentEvent,2015-04-18 16:32:46+00:00,23924195,Lasagne/Lasagne,43829,benanne,11752110,Lasagne,69322115,94179196,"Looks like Travis fails on Python 2 and Python 3, but for different reasons. On Python 2 it fails because there's a unicode character in a docstring somewhere. Python 2 requires the encoding to be declared in this case (see http://stackoverflow.com/questions/6289474/working-with-utf-8-encoding-in-python-source ).

