16320,IssueCommentEvent,2016-05-16 13:10:07+00:00,43645564,ganga-devs/ganga,1102021,rob-c,13271048,ganga-devs,155012086,219420829,"I would argue that this is read into an ordered dict so it only stores unique entries but we want to ensure we load the plugins in order. I don't know how ordered dict handles the same key twice but I imagine it reduces:
```Test:Dirac:LHCb:Dirac:Gaudi:LHCb``` to ```Test:Dirac:LHCb:Gaudi``` which isn't what we want. (although possibly harmless this still makes me very uncomfortable) unless we know that adding a new key changes the position of the dict entry in ```keys()```?",{},,User,False
