> So items[0] is Boots of Speed which only has a movespeed. It doesn't have
> mana regen or ability power or anything, so those numbers should be 0. The
> actual stats for these items that get returned from the Riot API is
> sometimes wrong, so we haven't put much time into making sure that Cass
> gives the correct values because Riot doesn't do it.
>
> That said, to prevent the AttributeError from occurring, you can use this
> line of code instead -- this will return 0 if the stat doesn't exist for
> that item.
>
> mana_regen = getattr(my_item, 'mana_regen', 0)
>
> You should just know that in some cases Riot gives the incorrect data, so
> don't rely on the data to be perfect.
