17461,IssueCommentEvent,2018-05-24 22:35:48+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,17223437,rigrassm,17889013,certbot,326194370,391886780,"Was just dealing with this and it turns out the issue for me was there was an existing txt record still in my domain's zone from when I had manually done the DNS challenge option the first time around. The API call used to delete that existing record is not providing the expected parameter for entity.change.deletions[0] so it's not able to delete the old entry.

I haven't dug into what exactly is expected in that API call so not sure what parameter isn't being provided correctly but you can work around this by deleting any old TXT records in the domain's zone that were used for the DNS challenge previously.

After that, certbot is able to add the TXT record and also removes it once it finishes so it shouldn't happen again.",{},NONE,User,False
