17491,IssueCommentEvent,2016-11-06 12:09:12+00:00,26516210,certbot/certbot,2247896,YuGiOhJCJ,17889013,certbot,187121800,258676836,"I installed them automatically from source code using my own scripts because I don't like SlackBuilds.
Indeed, the problem with SlackBuilds is that they require to be ""root"" to be able to run them whereas a lot of things can be done by a simple user.
But I like watching the content of SlackBuilds in order to make my own scripts because I can see how the program is built.
Sometimes I watch also how packages are built from other operating systems (like ArchLinux).

Anyway thank you I was not aware that augeas was a dependency of python-augeas.
So, I installed augeas and now the previous error has gone:
```
$ certbot --config-dir conf --logs-dir logs --work-dir work --apache
The apache plugin is not working; there may be problems with your existing configuration.
The error was: NoInstallationError('Cannot find Apache control command apache2ctl',)
```

The problem is just that apache2ctl is named apachectl on Slackware64.
So it should be easy to resolve.

Anyway, why apache2ctl is called?
I only want my certificates, I don't want to start/restart my webserver for that.
That's a bit weird that apache2ctl is called.

The same things happen when I use the certonly command:
```
$ certbot --config-dir conf --logs-dir logs --work-dir work --apache certonly
The apache plugin is not working; there may be problems with your existing configuration.
The error was: NoInstallationError('Cannot find Apache control command apache2ctl',)
```

Sorry, I am noob, it is the first time I use certbot and Let's Encrypt.",{},,User,False
