17602,IssueCommentEvent,2018-03-27 18:27:50+00:00,56847043,nfcpy/nfcpy,6604011,nehpetsde,18479744,nfcpy,308751853,376627564,"Thanks. The problem is that nfcpy tries to enable fast serial connection with 921.6 kbps which the RPi 3 can't handle on ttyS0. Unfortunately the logic to discover an RPi is based on the BCM270? silicon identifier that used to be in cpuinfo. Apparently this has changed to the BCM283? chip package identifier ([ref](https://raspberrypi.stackexchange.com/questions/840/why-is-the-cpu-sometimes-referred-to-as-bcm2708-sometimes-bcm2835)). I'll try to find a more robust way. Meantime, if you use the nfcpy git source, you can temporarily exchange ""BCM270"" with ""BCM283"" in [src/nfc/clf/pn532.py](https://github.com/nfcpy/nfcpy/blob/6ebb26b8f3a47183a66002b05a2c780a7e861b24/src/nfc/clf/pn532.py#L397).",{},OWNER,User,False
