17644,IssueCommentEvent,2018-03-16 00:01:22+00:00,101461719,dashingsoft/pyarmor,2036296,joonis,19261815,dashingsoft,304147686,373560569,"Users must also know that globals are mutable but locals are not. So you should always wrap the whole module within a function and just make public functions global:

```python
@wraparmor
def __load__():

    @wraparmor
    def my_private_func():
        pass

    global my_public_func
    @wraparmor
    def my_public_func():
        pass

__load__()
```",{},NONE,User,False
