18059,IssueCommentEvent,2018-06-19 21:23:02+00:00,72477752,pulumi/pulumi,1871912,swgillespie,21992475,pulumi,333829018,398550658,"Thanks for the issue!

If you want to deploy a JVM application to the cloud, you can do that today using any language that Pulumi supports. [Here is an example](https://github.com/pulumi/examples/tree/176ce60f95128f42afae86281eb7098d399c3743/aws-ts-serverless-raw) that deploys a serverless C# application using AWS Lambda and API Gateway, while writing the infrastructure code in TypeScript. In general, you are not required to write your Pulumi infrastructure code in the same language that your application is written in. The only exception to this is when you are using Pulumi ""closure serialization"" to deploy functions defined in your deployment code, which today is a Node.js only feature.

As for writing Pulumi deployment code itself in a JVM language, I know that I personally want this and have a branch that is a starter for a Java SDK for Pulumi. I would be happy to mentor and help out if anyone from the community wants to make a run at this. (See https://github.com/pulumi/pulumi/issues/1539 for a similar language support issue). I'm also working on it when I have free time but unfortunately I haven't been able to dedicate much time to it lately.
",{},MEMBER,User,False
