18254,IssueCommentEvent,2018-06-13 17:41:22+00:00,68402336,streamlink/streamlink,9669492,Vangelis66,22243823,streamlink,331839235,397024227,"@beardypig 
Hello 😃 
I urge you to be careful in the way you modify the ITV plugin...
For LIVE ITVHub streams, 
```
https://www.itv.com/hub/itv
https://www.itv.com/hub/itv2
https://www.itv.com/hub/itvbe
https://www.itv.com/hub/itv3
https://www.itv.com/hub/citv
https://www.itv.com/hub/itv4
```
streamlink still uses a legacy playlist API 
```
https://secure-mercury.itv.com/PlaylistService.svc?wsdl 
(=> http://tempuri.org/PlaylistService/GetPlaylist)
``` 
that returns RTMPE streams; 
at this time of posting, it appears that it is only for ITV1+ITV4 that the 
old API returns working streams (for the rest, you get errors of the type: 
```
[cli][error] Try 1/1: Could not open stream <RTMPStream({'rtmp': 'rtmpe://cp2739
90.live.edgefcs.net/live', 'app': 'live', 'playpath': 'itv3livefms_1200@s172816?
auth=eaEbxb5dHdkdlc2c4abcIapaKaOazcUaeaSclbGafaLdPdVaCapbNbxbOdgd9c4anam-bBit7x-
frG-dDLhFDnmw0Ebuavp&aifp=v001&slist=itv3livefms_1200@s172816', 'swfVfy': 'http:
//www.itv.com/mediaplayer/ITVMediaPlayer.swf', 'timeout': 10, 'live': True, 'flv
': '-'}, redirect=False> (No data returned from stream)
error: Could not open stream <RTMPStream({'rtmp': 'rtmpe://cp273990.live.edgefcs
.net/live', 'app': 'live', 'playpath': 'itv3livefms_1200@s172816?auth=eaEbxb5dHd
kdlc2c4abcIapaKaOazcUaeaSclbGafaLdPdVaCapbNbxbOdgd9c4anam-bBit7x-frG-dDLhFDnmw0E
buavp&aifp=v001&slist=itv3livefms_1200@s172816', 'swfVfy': 'http://www.itv.com/m
ediaplayer/ITVMediaPlayer.swf', 'timeout': 10, 'live': True, 'flv': '-'}, redire
ct=False>, tried 1 times, exiting
[cli][info] Closing currently open stream...
```
The advantage of the old live API is it can be accessed from overseas with a simple 
`--http-header ""X-Forwarded-For=<UK IP here>""`, while the FMS _does not geo-block_.
The disadvantage is that currently only one quality variant (1200k) is offered, for only two 
(ITV1+ITV4) of the channels... 😞 

Their new **Live channel API** is a total mess, if you ask me... 😠 For starters, it requires 
user authentication, but, to make matters worse, is not consistent across all channels...

Fot ITV1 and ITV4, they employ the following API: 
```
https://mediaplayer.itv.com/flash/playlists/ukonly/itv1.xml
https://mediaplayer.itv.com/flash/playlists/ukonly/itv4.xml
```
which, as expected, geo-blocks, but **can't be tricked with an X-F-F request header** 😢 ;
you need a full blown, whitelisted, UK HTTP(S) proxy to gain access to RTMPE (only) streams which, 
fortunately, are not (yet) geo-blocked but, again, only offer the 1200k variant...
Working cmd for ITV1+ITV4: 
```
rtmpdump -v -r ""rtmpe://cp532701.live.edgefcs.net/live"" -a ""live"" -f ""WIN 30,0,0,113"" -p ""https://www.itv.com/hub/itv"" -W ""http://www.itv.com/mediaplayer/ITVMediaPlayer.swf"" -y ""itv1static@45475"" -o ""itv1live_1200k.flv""

rtmpdump -v -r ""rtmpe://cp532702.live.edgefcs.net/live"" -a ""live"" -f ""WIN 30,0,0,113"" -p ""https://www.itv.com/hub/itv4"" -W ""http://www.itv.com/mediaplayer/ITVMediaPlayer.swf"" -y ""itv4static@45482"" -o ""itv4live_1200k.flv"" 
```
In a random fashion, and for **ITV1 only**, I was served AdobeHDS streams, unencrypted, 
of the following manifest: 
`https://itv1livehds-lh.akamaihd.net/z/itv1livehds_1@321229/manifest.f4m?hdcore=3.11`
That manifest is geo-blocked, but can be tricked with a X_F_F header; advantage over the RTMPE 
stream is it offers 5 variants, higher quality one being 1800k ! 👍 

For the rest of the Live channels, they employ `*magni.itv.com/playlist/itvonline/*` playlist API URL, 
which can be tricked (X-F-F) to divulge live stream data...
On a desktop browser, these are MPEG-DASH streams served from 
```
itv2simadotcom.akamaized.net
itvbesimadotcom.akamaized.net
itv3simadotcom.akamaized.net
citvsimadotcom.akamaized.net
```
hosts which **all geo-block** and, to add insult to injury, **all use Common Encryption** (cenc) 
with Widevine DRM 👎 :angry: ; ITV2 example: 
```json
      ""Base"" : ""https://itv2simadotcom.akamaized.net/"",
      ""MediaFiles"" : [
        {
          ""Href"" : ""playout/itv2/cenc.isml/.mpd?hdnea=st=1522019201~exp=1522040801~acl=/*~data=nohubplus~hmac=df9af29ad634c2e5ee82785ef00da299ea453e6821bb4fbd51af5846ff5e0af2"",
          ""KeyServiceUrl"" : ""https://itvpnp.live.ott.irdeto.com/Widevine/getlicense?CrmId=itvpnp&AccountId=itvpnp&ContentId=itv2""
        }
```
I don't know whether streamlink can do anything about these live ITV streams, given the stance 
of the main repo owner with regards to DRM... 
Addendum: Just the other day I was offered, **just for ITV2**, unencrypted AdobeHDS streams, 
of the following manifest: 
`https://itv2livehds-lh.akamaihd.net/z/itv2livehds_1@321228/manifest.f4m?hdcore=3.11`
with the same limitations and features as the ITV1 manifest quoted previously in this comment; 
but it cannot be returned by their API in a reproducible fashion... 

I was unsuccessful in discovering AppleHLS streams for ITVHub Live streams; spoofing a mobile 
browser UA, I was always offered to install their Android/iOS app, so this is left to others to test...

VOD ITVHub streams were previously discussed in https://github.com/streamlink/streamlink/issues/1436; I was of the first to point out they were deprecating RTMPE streams and moving on to encrypted (cenc) DASH on desktop and encrypted AES-128 HLS on mobile platforms...
While I think a ""_fix_"" for ClearKey would be awesome, for VOD on the ITVhub the quickest approach 
would be to explore existing HLS streams for mobile, a la [youtube-dl](https://github.com/rg3/youtube-dl/blob/master/youtube_dl/extractor/itv.py) ...

Closing this, let me stress once again that my original intention is **NOT** piracy 
(as I believe is also the case with 99% of streamlink users...); I have an old laptop, 
with an old CPU, a very old integrated GPU without hardware decoding capabilities 
for the h264 codec, using streamlink is one of the few solutions I have for watching 
in a comfortable manner on-line media content (fetching to disk and watching via a 
dedicated media player, making use of DXVA features...). 
As such, my heartfelt gratitude goes to all devs keeping this project alive!",{},NONE,User,False
18256,IssueCommentEvent,2017-04-10 08:55:52+00:00,68402336,streamlink/streamlink,6311872,Germandrummer92,22243823,streamlink,218797576,292889322,"Actually, if you put the default-stream into the streamlinkrc you don't have to retype the argument for every function you define (if you're like me and have different ones for example and are even too lazy to type the argument in your zshrc/bashrc :smile: ).

Also, for completeness sake here is the function I use. It also autocompletes my stream names to twitch if it doesnt include a ""/"" (e.g. any other url will just be passed through).
`wt() {
     url=""$1""
     if [[ ""$url"" =~ "".*twitch.*"" || ""$url"" =~ "".*/.*"" ]]; then
         streamlink ""$url"" ""${@:2}""
     else
         streamlink ""twitch.tv/$url"" ""${@:2}""
     fi
 }`

This means, that
`wt twitch.tv/ppd` and
`wt ppd` will work.

Thanks for all the help though :+1: ",{},,User,False
