> .
>
",{},NONE,User,False
18634,IssueCommentEvent,2017-11-13 05:55:25+00:00,102692863,onnx/onnx,17890620,dzhulgakov,31675368,onnx,273107310,343821361,"Proposal sound reasonable.

For input/output names they are currently serve purely descriptive purposes and don't get serialized in models. Thus we can freely rename them for consistency.

Attributes do get serialized and thus 'axis/axes' is a breaking change. In terms of naming - the only attribute that doesn't adhere to your proposal is `transA/transB` on `Gemm`. Not sure whether we want to change those.",{},OWNER,User,False
18637,IssueCommentEvent,2017-12-06 21:48:12+00:00,102692863,onnx/onnx,10075881,gramalingam,31675368,onnx,273775187,349785692,"What I meant was that a ""complete file path"" has disadvantages (lack of portability). A ""relative file path"" is better (but the interpretation of what this is relative to is determined by the execution environment anyway; relative to the ONNX model file makes sense, but the ONNX model location is external to the model itself). The final choice is a container format, formalized. Each seems to have its detractors.

Another way around the problem is to make all such externalized tensors additional ""inputs"" of the model, and just use the execution API provided to execute the model. Externalizing tensors anyway requires some support from the ONNX exporter of whatever framework the user uses (or a separate ONNX utility), so making such tensors as additional inputs can be done there. This doesn't require changes to ONNX itself.",{},COLLABORATOR,User,False
