18729,IssueCommentEvent,2018-06-25 23:07:17+00:00,2811323,oauthlib/oauthlib,39317519,claweyenuk,33832354,oauthlib,335519524,400123573,"Ah, sorry, I realized my last paragraph was not that clear and I missed some important information.

So the DB has the authorized date for each token, and the reason it's there is so that a user can see all the tokens they've approved and when.

But in `save_bearer_token()` which handles writing to the DB, that info isn't readily available, so to get that info there I put that info in `flask.g` and look it up in `save_bearer_token()` just before writing.

I think it'd be nice if the auth code or refresh token info was passed to the `save_bearer_token` function somehow so that information can be persisted on these tokens even through a refresh.  That said, I do have a workaround, it's just not as explicit as I would like.",{},NONE,User,False
